    "richtext_GyAU6y": {
      "type": "richtext",
      "name": "Rich text",
      "settings": {
        "heading": "",
        "subheading": "",
        "text_content": "<p>At <strong>SVELDA</strong>, we view the home as a curated ecosystem where the permanent and the ephemeral exist in perfect equilibrium. While our textiles provide the soft, bioactive climate for rest, our stone collection provides the architectural foundation. These are not merely vessels; they are deliberate mineral anchors designed to ground a room. Each piece is a functional sculpture—a fragment of Earth’s deep history, meticulously finished and plated for the modern interior.</p><p>The integration of natural stone into the domestic environment serves a purpose beyond the aesthetic. In a world of synthetic surfaces, the raw mineralogy of marble and limestone offers an honest, cooling touch that benefits both the creature and the curator. These stones act as silent guardians of the home's temperature, remaining refreshingly cool in the height of summer and retaining a steady, comforting presence in the winter. From the crystalline luminosity of Italian calcite to the tectonic weight of Spanish breccia, our collection is a study in geological contrast, intended to harmonize with the most sophisticated textures of contemporary design.</p>",
        "text_alignment": "left",
        "enable_read_more": false,
